Nigeria Cancels Nitel Sale to New Generation, Thisday Reports

-- B y   S a m   O l u k o y a
-- 
2011-02-18T07:57:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-18/nigeria-cancels-nitel-sale-to-new-generation-thisday-reports.html
  Nigeria ’s government cancelled the
sale of state-owned Nigerian Telecommunications Ltd. and its
mobile unit Mtel to New Generation,  ThisDay  said, citing the
director-general of the Bureau of Public Enterprises, Bola
Onagoruwa.  New Generation was unable to meet the payment terms for the
company, known as Nitel, Onagoruwa told lawmakers, the Lagos-
based newspaper reported.  New Generation, which includes China Unicom   Hong Kong )
Ltd., Minerva Group of Dubai and Nigeria’s GiCell Wireless Ltd.,
missed a deadline to pay the initial $750 million of its $2.5
billion bid after the sale was approved on Oct. 12.  Chukwuma Nwakoh, spokesman for the Bureau of Public
Enterprises, said by phone from the capital, Abuja, that he
couldn’t confirm the cancellation of the sale.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sam Olukoya in Lagos at 
 solukoya2@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 